Questions:
What is the primary goal of the ProtECtion Study described in the consent form?
A) To evaluate the long-term survival rates of breast cancer patients;
B) To assess the effectiveness of Crocin in protecting cardiovascular function in breast cancer patients undergoing radiotherapy and chemotherapy;
C) To compare the efficacy of different chemotherapy drugs;
D) To study the impact of echocardiography technology on breast cancer treatment.

Correct answer: B

Which of the following interventions is considered experimental in the ProtECtion Study for breast cancer patients undergoing radiotherapy and chemotherapy?
A) Routine physical examinations and blood chemistry tests;
B) Use of echocardiography and electrocardiogram for monitoring cardiac function;
C) Administration of crocin total glucoside tablets during radiotherapy and chemotherapy;
D) Collection of blood and urine samples for routine safety monitoring.

Correct answer: C
